From 08da5c4d9776b78e8bc82bb4eb596172d11c5a6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KRT <krt@local>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 16:15:44 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Strip Application Insights instrumentation keys; KRT
 no-telemetry stance
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- 11 built-in extension package.json files: aiKey value emptied
  (was a shared Microsoft Application Insights instrumentation key,
  0c6ae...7255). vscode-extension-telemetry's TelemetryReporter handles
  empty key gracefully — no network calls.

- src/vs/platform/telemetry/common/telemetryService.ts: replace the
  Settings UI 'Read more about [data we collect](aka.ms/vscode-telemetry)'
  message with 'KRT does not collect telemetry. This setting has no
  effect.' Honest and drops the aka.ms URL from the binary.
